15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.9c of Title 70, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Growing
20 Minds, Active Kids Act".
21 B. It is the intention of the Oklahoma State Legislature
22 through this act to focus on daily recess as essential for students
23 as it provides a necessary break from academic work, allowing
24 students to recharge both mentally and physically. Physical
Req. No. 12978 Page 1

1 acti vity during recess helps improve focus, reduce stress, and
2 support overall physical health. It also encourages social
3 interaction where children learn important skills like teamwork,
4 conflict resolution, and communication. By giving students adequate
5 time to play and unwind, recess fosters better behavior in the
6 classroom and enhances students' ability to concentrate and learn
7 effectively.
8 C. As used in this section:
9 1. "Daily recess" means a scheduled break or breaks during the
10 school day that will allow students to engage in unstructured free
11 play or physical activity;
12 2. "District board of education" means the governing board of
13 each school district in Oklahoma; and
14 3. "Physical activity" means any bodily movement that uses
15 energy and is produced by skeletal muscles.
16 D. School districts shall incorporate physical activity into
17 the school day by providing at least thirty (30) minutes for daily
18 recess to students in full-day prekindergarten, kindergarten, and
19 grades one through five. For grades six through eight, at least
20 thirty (30) minutes for daily recess is strongly recommended. Each
21 district board of education shall establish the timing of the daily
22 recess. The daily recess required by this subsection may be broken
23 up into segments that best fit the schedules of each school
24 district.
Req. No. 12978 Page 2

1 1. The daily recess provided for in this section shall be in
2 addition to the weekly sixty (60) minute physical education
3 requirements set forth in subsections B and C of Section 11-103.9 of
4 Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
5 2. The daily recess shall occur outside the school building
6 unless weather or other conditions require it to occur inside.
7 3. For students with disabilities, the daily recess shall
8 comply with the individualized education program (IEP) or Section
9 504 plan of the student.
10 4. Virtual charter schools shall be exempt from the
11 requirements of this section.
12 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
